  "text": "Thirdly, we propose a variant of U-Net (one type of FCN [CITATION_1] ) to analyze the normalized range-doppler spectrums obtained from the signal preprocessing block. The proposed network firstly detect presence of objects in the foreground. If an object is identified, the network then further estimates its azimuth and elevation to fully determine its 3D location. As an example, we successfully trained the radar system for detecting and estimating the 3D position of a car in a noisy environment.",
